As an introverted creative entrepreneur who places a high value on privacy, running a business shouldn't feel so awkward, but sometimes it does. Most online resources and mentors tell you to engage with large (evil) tech companies in an outgoing manner. Adhere to the algorithms here, share your personal charm. Get verified on that service, stay online 24/7, answer questions with your own videos, and reply immediately. Videos, videos, still videos.
One-third
For me, this year is a year of transformation.
I no longer want to献 my money, data, and energy to large tech companies, nor do I want to listen to mentors who only apply a one-size-fits-all outgoing solution to everyone. I am exploring new business models while also working to overcome my long-held belief that success can only be achieved by doing things in a specific way.
Good luck to me!
The first step has been taken.
I have exited FB, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and注销了我的个人WhatsApp账户.I have logged out of my personal WhatsApp account.
Yesterday, I also removed the last external tracker from my website - Google Analytics, and felt great about it.
To better support GDPR, I recently subscribed to a European CRM service and will migrate my business over in the coming weeks.
I transferred the MX records to Proton and now have full SPF, DKIM, and DMARC, without having to pay Google for basic email verification.
3/3
