Website: You might want to check out @user5. It seems easy to use and has a nice interface, plus it's open-source. I plan to migrate one of my websites over before the next renewal.
Signal: Check out cal.com. It's an open-source calendar service that integrates scheduling for video calls via Element, JITSI, etc. It also supports Signal, but I haven't tested whether it's just for messaging or video calls.
